text: New Year's Smash (January 2021) was a two-part professional wrestling show made by All Elite Wrestling (AEW). It took place on January 6 and 7, 2021 at the Daily's Place in Jacksonville, Florida. The event aired as special episodes of Dynamite. It was the first New Year's Smash event held by AEW. The event was originally supposed to take place on December 30, 2020, and end on January 6, 2021 but the event was pushed back a week. The Brodie Lee Celebration of Life event took its place to honor the memory of AEW wrestler Brodie Lee who died on December 26. Night 1's main event saw Kenny Omega defeat Rey Fenix to keep his AEW World Championship. Omega hit Fénix with the One-Winged Angel and got the pinfall victory. Night 2's main event saw Darby Allin defeat Brian Cage to keep his AEW TNT Championship.
